		///////////////////////////// confirmationControl example

		if (selector == 0 && confirmationControl == 3) {
			Board.text = "You give it a good amount of time to think about it, but you want to maintain the most of the sanity possible on the students. Maybe the laws can be different, but the classes of today have been perfected by generations of scholars and professors. It would be truly a waste to drop them just like that. So, you tell Celia that she should keep the original faculty, as you know that there will be tough times ahead, and she requires a reliable staff in times to come. Besides, they can help her to keep her ground and stop getting too far into the corruption that seems to be seeping through all the high spheres of the city. She raises both of her eyebrows. <i>“It seems that my liege has a plan already for the city. Mmmmm. Okay, if that’s what you think then It’s settled then. I’ll make sure to keep them in the line.”</i> She nods but waves a hand. <i>“And the thing about keeping my ground, I’ll see what happens. Maybe I’ll unbalance the whole scale. I tend to change things when I’m involved in everything”</i> She runs a hand through her other arm slowly.\n\nThe door sounds a couple of times, the distinct echo of someone knocking it mildly. Both of you turn to see as the door opens, revealing a small figure of a man sheepishly opening the door. When he sees both of you, he says in a barely audible tone. <i>“A-Are you busy then?”</i> To which Celia sighs and nods. <i>“Yeah, of course I’m busy, I’m at work after all, Mus.”</i> You can see that there was a man that is the living image of the weak will. Lower shoulder-line, avoiding eyes, shrunken body over itself. <i>“I wanted you to know that I found out another method… But I’ll tell you at a better moment. Excuse me…”</i> He says before closing the door slowly, without making much sound. Celia places one hand over her forehead at the same time that you ask her who he is and what method he was talking about. <i>“Oh right. He is my husband, the one I talked you about…”</i> You can see why she said that he is comfy. <i>“And the method… We’ve had some troubles conceiving and we’re been trying everything for it. I blame him for it, that’s one thing for sure. ”</i>  To which she turns to you, as if she just noticed something. <i>“But you’re the liege of the city. Maybe you can help us with that. If someone must have the most qualified alchemist in the city, must be the liege. So, if you know anything about a treatment that could prove useful for both of us, then I’ll make sure that its properly paid”</i> She says with a wink. After that, both of you take your time in finishing the details of the deal with the old teachers before you call it a day and return to your castle.";
			endTurnFun ();
			NPCCharList.CharFollower [iCelia].corruptionStage -= 1; 
			QuestControl.celiaQuest = 4;
			return;
		}

		if (selector == 1 && confirmationControl == 3) {
			Board.text = "You think that its about time the university has a new change of course. And the new teachers are the best way to get into that path with the students. There are new fields of study and ways of teaching that could spark the rebellious nature of the young people in the city. And in the times ahead, you will require more people to be unhappy with the situation of the Citadel. So, you tell Celia that its time to change most of the faculty, that maybe she should see who of them are able to adapt to the new times and fire the other ones. You tell her that there will be times ahead when the Citadel is going to try and recove their conquered city, and maybe if they have students that are rebellious by nature, they will be less influenced by the ways of the capital. That she has the liberty to continue doing what she loves to do in the university, and that you encourage her ner course of action. She claps several times. <i>“That’s what I wanted to hear, my liege! I knew that I could count on you on that. I knew that you had that edge on doing the most interesting things around.”</i> \n\nAs both of you finished with the details, the door sounds a couple of times, the distinct echo of someone knocking it mildly. Both of you turn to see as the door opens, revealing a small figure of a man sheepishly opening the door. When he sees both of you, he says in a barely audible tone. <i>“A-Are you busy then?”</i> To which Celia sighs and nods. <i>“Yeah, of course I’m busy, I’m at work after all, Mus.”</i> You can see that there was a man that is the living image of the weak will. Lower shoulder-line, avoiding eyes, shrunken body over itself. <i>“I wanted you to know that I found out another method… But I’ll tell you at a better moment. Excuse me…”</i> He says before closing the door slowly, without making much sound. Celia places one hand over her forehead at the same time that you ask her who he is and what method he was talking about. <i>“Oh right. He is my husband, the one I talked you about…”</i> You can see why she said that he is comfy. <i>“And the method… We’ve had some troubles conceiving and we’re been trying everything for it. I blame him for it, that’s one thing for sure. ”</i>  To which she turns to you, as if she just noticed something. <i>“But you’re the liege of the city. Maybe you can help us with that. If someone must have the most qualified alchemist in the city, must be the liege. So, if you know anything about a treatment that could prove useful for both of us, then I’ll make sure that its properly paid”</i> She says with a wink. After that, both of you take your time in finishing the details of the deal with the old teachers before you call it a day and return to your castle.";
			endTurnFun ();
