		if (selector == 0 && confirmationControl == 4) {
			Board.text = "You walk beside her and see that the campus is still calm even when you know that there will be a small group of people outside the office soon enough. You tell her that she shouldn’t hide what she is. She is amazing and gets the work done just like she is. That she has your support on all of this, as you understand what its to be against all odds. She is surprised from your words but pokes your side with her elbow. <i>“Hey, that’s nice coming from you. Maybe I was wrong about you after all. You didn’t jump ship at the first sight of problems and that is a good sign.”</i> You tell her that if you were planning to jump ship, you wouldn’t be even there, she has been quite the bitch with you after all.\n\nShe laughs from that. <i>“I must admit that’s true. I can be a bitch sometimes.”</i> Sometimes? You tell her that she should turn down her bitch lever once in a while. <i>“Oh fuck off, you’re not that saint that you think you are. You’re like me, you just are good at hiding it. But maybe I’ll cut you some slack…”</i> It seems that she is reluctant to stop being so bossy with you, but at least she is thinking about taking it easier and that’s one battle won from the war that is Celia. You tell her that when they come, she can say that she has the support of the authority in this situation and that she is free to send them to you in your castle. You’ll be quite happy to see that their pleas are answered and that everything will be fixed in due time. <i>“Oh. How much I would pay to be there when you speak with them, if they have the guts to bring this to you.”</i> \n\nAfter a couple of minutes of planning about what are you going to do, you leave her to get ready for whatever is about to happen. You leave to your castle to get ready for anyone who has enough courage to go with you. ";
