		if (selector == 1 && confirmationControl == 4) {
			Board.text = "You tell her as you approach into her direction that its a good time to change her ways. Both of you look outside, as its still quite calm even when you know what is happening at the university right now. This is a wake up call, and you will help her to return to her once good ways of being. You tell her that you can help her to get out of this situation, after all you’re the liege and your help could prove quite valuable in her pursue of getting out of there as clean as possible, but you need to see her try to change back into the disciplined dean that she was before all of this. You know that she does an amazing work at the university and you can’t think of anyone else who could be better for the job than her and that’s why you’re thinking on lending your hand to her.  <i>“You’re quite the charmer with your words on that. Its not as if I have a better option, am I?”</i> She chuckles at her own words, but still looking at the campus for a bit.\n";
			NPCCharList.CharFollower [iCelia].corruptionStage -= 2; 
			if (NPCCharList.CharFollower [iCelia].corruptionStage > 0) {
				Board.text = "She shakes her head at your offer. <i>“I’m too corrupted to even think of a way to reach at that state. I’ve been like this for so long, and I’ve been surrounded by those kind of people several times. This is what I am right now and there is no turning back from it.”</i> She turns to see you and shrugs. <i>“I guess its time to fight back with all I got. I’ll pull out all the favors I have and see what happens.”</i> You sigh, as you tell her that you’ll help her. Maybe not as direct as you thought at first, but you’ll be sure that she isn’t all alone in this situation, she’s the best dean that you’ve known, after all. <i>“And I think the only one. But hey, thanks for the leverage at least. You’re not that bad as the others said you were”</i> You shake hands with her and give her some advice of what she should be saying to the ones that would come to her. \n\nYou can help her walk in the walk, but she’s the one that decided her course after all. And with that, you wave her goodbye and return to your castle, sending a courier to be waiting for news about the Dean as soon as it gets it.";
			} else {
				Board.text = "She nods at your offer. <i>“I’m pretty sure that I can do it. I think that this is my last chance to get off this madness and return to a semblance of normalcy.”</i> She turns to see you. <i>“You’re sure as stubborn as a mule, "+ GameControl.playerName +", but I thank the gods that you’re like that right now. You’re one of the persons that are still sane in this city of crazy people. If I can come out clean of this, I’ll promise that I’ll never return to that. I don’t want to leave the university to another dean that will cut it even before I can say ‘Sucking Citadel’s cock’”</i> She crosses her arms. That’s what you wanted to hear. You tell her that you can help her to get ready, and tell her to send them to you if they get too hard to reason with. You’ll be happy to talk with them about how you’re a valuable part of the city and cut a deal with them. That she doesn’t have to worry, as long as she keeps her part of the deal. <i>“I may be bitchy, but I’m not one to broke promises that easily, not without a good reason at least”</i> \n\nAnd with that, both of you get ready for when the relatives of the students come. When you’re sure that she is ready to meet them, you excuse yourself and go back to the castle and get ready for whoever could get past Celia’s sharp tongue. Because if anyone does, it will be truly a terrifying foe indeed.";
			}

			endTurnFun ();
			QuestControl.celiaQuest = 5;
			return;
		}
