		if (selector == 0 && confirmationControl == 5) {
			Board.text = "You walk beside her and see that the campus is still calm even when you know that there will be a small group of people outside the office soon enough. You tell her that its good to see that she isn’t afraid to clean her past. Its nice to see that she is trying to return to the old ways of being, that takes a lot of effort and courage. You tell her that she has your support on all of this, as you understand what its to be against all odds, especially when it means to fight back the corruption in the city. She is surprised from your words but pokes your side with her elbow. <i>“Thanks my liege. It seems that was wrong about you after all. You didn’t jump ship at the first sight of problems and that is a good sign. You sure love to prove me wrong, huh?”</i> You tell her that if you were planning to jump ship, you wouldn’t be even there, she has been quite the bitch with you after all.\n\nShe laughs from that. <i>“I must admit that’s true. I can be a bitch sometimes.”</i> Sometimes? You tell her that she should turn down her bitch lever once in a while. <i>“Oh come on, I’m just severe, that’s all. I’m pretty sure that you must be severe sometimes with your staff and others. Its not easy being the leader of a large group of people, we can both agree on that. One weakness and they’ll jump all over you with two fingers snapped. But hey, maybe I overdid it with you. I haven’t forgotten about Virgil by the way”</i> It seems that she is reluctant to stop being so bossy with you, but at least she is thinking about taking it easier and that’s one battle won from the war that is Celia. You tell her that when they come, she can say that she has the support of the authority in this situation and that she is free to send them to you in your castle. You’ll be quite happy to see that their pleas are answered and that everything will be fixed in due time. <i>“Thanks. I’ll do my best to live out your expectations about my sanity. I won’t promise I’ll be the best, but 